bles us to see how the key concepts of openness—including collaboration, ad-hocracy, and the splitting of contested projects through “forking”—play out in reality. The resulting book is the richest critical analysis of openness to date, one that roots media theory in messy reality and thereby helps us move beyond the vaporware promises of digital utopians and take the first steps toward truly understanding what openness does, and does not, have to offer.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAuthorshipxCollaborationxSocial aspects. 0aCommunities of practice. 0aUser-generated contentxSocial aspects. 0aWikipedia / Social aspectsxAuthorship / Collaboration / Social aspectsxUser-generated content / Social aspectsxCommunities of practice. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aopenness, wikipedia, decision making, transparency, politics, business, organizational structure, user access levels, article deletion policies, edit wars, internet, information age, encyclopedia, reference, ad-hocracy, collaboration, media theory, authorship, community, user-generated content, archives, controversy, nonfiction.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226192444423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226192444/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles